Source: argm
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/bashtanov/argm

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-argm
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-argm
Depends: ${postgresql:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: Argmax, argmin, and anyold aggregates for PostgreSQL
 argm provides polymorphic aggregates that return the value associated with
 the greatest or least sorting key, plus an efficient arbitrary-value aggregate.
